#: ../../../api/cursors.rst:181
msgid ""
"This command is similar to execute + iter; however it supports endless data "
"streams. The feature is not available in PostgreSQL, but some "
"implementations exist: Materialize `SUBSCRIBE`__ and CockroachDB "
"`CHANGEFEED`__ for instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/cursors.rst:186
msgid ""
"The feature, and the API supporting it, are still experimental. Beware... 👀"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/cursors.rst:192
msgid ""
"The parameters are the same of `execute()`, except for `size` which can be "
"used to set results retrieval by chunks instead of row-by-row."
msgstr ""

